input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: SAINT-MAURICE TOWN HALL - MUNICIPALITY OF SAINT-MAURICE. Summary: Maintenance of Sanitation Networks and Equipment in Municipal Buildings. Description: The purpose of the contract is the preventive and curative maintenance of the sanitation networks of municipal facilities in the town of Saint-Maurice. The contract is concluded at mixed prices. All scheduled preventive maintenance services are remunerated by application of a global and fixed price. Additional preventive maintenance interventions and curative maintenance interventions, paid for by application of unit prices, appear in the Unit Price Schedule (BPU). These services will give rise to the establishment of a framework agreement concluded without a minimum annual amount and with a maximum annual amount: 40,000 euros excluding VAT or 160,000 euros excluding VAT overall. The service contract is concluded for an initial period of 12 months and is tacitly renewable 3 times without its maximum duration exceeding 4 years.. Published Date: 2025-11-08. Description: The Syndicat Mixte Entre Pic et Etang (SMEPE) exercises waste treatment competence for the 6 member groups of municipalities: Community of Agglomeration of Pays de l'Or; Community of Municipalities of Grand Pic St Loup; Community of Agglomeration of Lunel; Community of Communes Rhôny Vistre Vidourle; Community of Communes of the Pays de Sommières; Community of Communes Terre de Camargue. Its territory brings together 89 municipalities representing approximately 223,000 sedentary inhabitants of the South-East sector of Hérault and the South-West sector of Gard.
